column4: UPDATE 4-Tesla shareholders approve CEO Musk's $2.6 bln compensation plan
column5: SAN FRANCISCO/BOSTON  March 21 Shareholders of electric car company Tesla Inc approved a compensation package potentially worth $2.6 billion for Chief Executive Officer Elon Musk on Wednesday  though by a lower margin than U.S. CEOs typically receive on pay votes.

column4: BRIEF-Tesla Says 96.8 Mln Votes Were Cast In Favor Of CEO Elon Musk's Compensation Plan

column4: Inability to audit U.S. elections a 'national security concern': Homeland chief
column5: WASHINGTON Not having a verifiable way to audit election results in some states represents a "national security concern " the Trump administration's homeland security chief said on Wednesday  looking ahead to U.S. midterm elections in November. | Video
